<title>UK: British Airways up on upbeat press comment.</title>
<headline>British Airways up on upbeat press comment.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in British Airways climbed 9-1/2p to 640 by 0920 GMT on Monday, bolstered by positive press comments, dealers said.  </p>
<p>The shares, just 6p from their record peaks, were supported by upbeat comments in the Financial Times' influential Lex Column, they said.</p>
<p>The report said the shares look cheap and there appears to be little chance the U.S. will kill its proposed alliance with American Airlines. --London newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
